    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Albuquerque</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Big 1 Reconstruction Team official Patti R Watson leter on Catherine C Robbins' August 20 travel article recommends alternate route that bypasses construction zone in Albuquerque, NM (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Re your coverage of the Big I Reconstruction Project in Albuquerque, N.M., ''Road Work Could Slow New Mexico Tourists,'' (Aug. 20) by Catherine C. Robbins, we recommend that visitors stay on I-25 and I-40 whenever possible rather than using city streets to bypass the construction zone. Traffic on city streets is already congested. We also recommend that visitors allow an extra 15 to 20 minutes to reach their destinations.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Re your coverage of the Big I Reconstruction Project in Albuquerque, N.M., ''Road Work Could Slow New Mexico Tourists,'' (Aug. 20) by Catherine C. Robbins, we recommend that visitors stay on I-25 and I-40 whenever possible rather than using city streets to bypass the construction zone. Traffic on city streets is already congested. We also recommend that visitors allow an extra 15 to 20 minutes to reach their destinations.</p>
        <p>Specific alternative routes for nighttime closings are available at www.thebigi.com.</p>
        <p>PATTI R. WATSON  Big I Reconstruction Team  Albuquerque</p>
      </block>
